  "text": "Logistic regression does not impose any restrictions on the types of explanatory variables considered [CITATION_1] . The explanatory variables considered in the present investigation involve three types of scales: categorical, ordinal and interval. The adolescent's service knowledge is an interval variable, classified in the present investigation in a Likert scale with seven points from completely disagree (1) to completely agree (7). The mother's occupational status corresponds to an ordinal variable, classified in the present investigation with three categories: high, low and domestic.",
